A study published in The Lancet revealed that men with short telomeres had a higher risk of heart disease, but statins provided protection.
Another study found a gene variant that increases women's risk of heart disease.
Gum disease was linked to pancreatic cancer, while stress in childhood was tied to heart disease later in life.
Air pollution poses a greater risk to postmenopausal women for cardiovascular disease.
National Wear Red for Women Day kicks off a campaign to raise awareness.
Overall, research highlights the importance of early detection and prevention strategies for heart disease.
